1 (3) Require mandatory quarantine, remediation, or
2 depopulation of any aquatic animals determined to pose
3 a biological aquatic risk."
4 SECTION 2. Section 141-51, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
5 amended by adding three new definitions to be appropriately
6 inserted and to read as follows:
7 ""Aquatic livestock" means species of domesticated or non­
8 native fish, crustaceans, and mollusks that are propagated and
9 raised for food or similar human food production, ecological
10 restoration, or similar commercial purposes.
11 "Biocontainment" means the operational methods, procedures,
12 physical facility features, and containment or safety equipment
13 or the designs thereof, used for managing infectious or
14 potentially hazardous materials and animals in an aquatic
15 livestock facility or environment in which these materials and
16 animals are potentially handled or maintained. "Biocontainment"
17 includes measures to prevent the release of infectious animal
18 species and associated pathogens into the natural environment.
19 "Biological aquatic risk" means the combination of the
20 consequences of an event, the probability of an adverse
21 biological event, and the magnitude of its potential
