1 consequences, where biological material constitutes the source
2 of harm, whether from an escaped aquatic livestock species or
3 associated pathogens or disease."
4 SECTION 3. Section 141-52, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
5 amended by amending subsection (a) to read as follows:
6 "(a) There is established within the department an
7 aquaculture program that shall:
8 (1) Monitor actions taken by industry and by federal,
9 state, county, and private agencies in activities
10 relating to aquaculture, and promote and support
11 worthwhile aquaculture activities;
12 (2) Serve as an information clearinghouse for aquaculture
13 activities;
14 (3) Coordinate development projects to investigate and
15 solve biological and technical problems involved in
16 raising selected species with commercial potential;
17 (4) Actively seek federal funding for aquaculture
18 activities;
19 (5) Undertake activities required to develop and expand
20 the aquaculture industry [•;—a-nd] , which shall include:
