3 The board may employ on a full or part-time basis
4 veterinarians and poultry inspectors, subject to chapter 76, to
5 carry out a uniform inspection system of poultry or poultry
6 products throughout the State. All poultry inspectors shall be
7 under the supervision and control of a veterinarian employed by
8 the board."
9 SECTION 5. (a) The division of animal industry shall
10 develop a biological aquatic risk-based framework for the
11 evaluation and authorization process to import and transport
12 aquatic livestock within the State. In developing the
13 framework, the division of animal industry shall consider:
14 (1) Relevant standards promulgated or recognized by the
15 United States Department of Agriculture;
16 (2) Current aquatic livestock import policies, disease
17 risks, and industry development issues;
18 (3) Best practices of the aquaculture industry, including
19 internationally recognized biosecurity and disease
20 management protocols; and
